The article discusses the power and impact of Black music on American culture. It emphasizes how Black music has shaped various genres, from rhythm and blues to jazz, gospel, country, rap, and more. The article recognizes the historical significance of Black music in expressing the hopes and struggles of a resilient people, from spirituals during slavery to jazz and Motown during the Civil Rights movement. It also highlights the influence of Black artists on musicians of all backgrounds and their role in reflecting societal issues and advocating for equality. The article concludes with President Biden proclaiming June 2022 as Black Music Appreciation Month, calling for the honoring of Black musicians and raising awareness and appreciation of Black music.